        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 5:15PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 515 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burgess, or near John W Kyle State Park, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oxford, Holly Springs National Forest, Harmontown, Burgess,
Abbeville, Malone, College Hill Station, Blackwater, College Hill,
Teckville, Hayes Crossing, and Spraggins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
